=head1 DESCRIPTION

Indicates an event you would like to subscribe and get notification
for. Currently, Resilience Hub supports notifications only for B<Drift
detected> and B<Scheduled assessment failure> events.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> EventType => Str

The type of event you would like to subscribe and get notification for.
Currently, Resilience Hub supports notifications only for B<Drift
detected> (C<DriftDetected>) and B<Scheduled assessment failure>
(C<ScheduledAssessmentFailure>) events.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Name => Str

Unique name to identify an event subscription.


=head2 SnsTopicArn => Str

Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Amazon Simple Notification Service
topic. The format for this ARN is:
C<arn:partition:sns:region:account:topic-name>. For more information
about ARNs, see Amazon Resource Names (ARNs)
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/aws-arns-and-namespaces.html)
in the I<Amazon Web Services General Reference> guide.



